[metadata]
Name:Ivory Tower Hand-Size Life Gain
Goal:Win
Turns:3
Difficulty:Easy
Description:Ivory Tower ("At the beginning of your upkeep, you gain X life, where X is the number of cards in your hand minus 4"). P0 controls an Ivory Tower and holds 6 cards. At the beginning of P0's upkeep the trigger gains 6 - 4 = 2 life (life: 20 -> 22). Before the fix the triggered GainLife converter hardcoded the amount to 1 (LifeAmount$ X failed to parse), so the player gained only 1 life. The amount reads only the public hand SIZE (CR 119; information-independent for network determinism) and is clamped to >= 0 (CR 119.4).

